## 1. DEFINITIONS

**1.1 "License"** means this document, *Aevum‑Meridian Economic License, Version 1.0*.

**1.2 "Systems"** means Aevum and Meridian, including all source code, object code, whitepapers, economic models, smart contracts, race contracts, governance artifacts, documentation, configuration files, and associated files distributed under this License.

**1.3 "You"** (or **"Your"**) means an individual or legal entity exercising rights under this License.

**1.4 "Contributor"** means any person or entity that creates, contributes to, or modifies the Systems and submits such Contribution under this License.

**1.5 "Contribution"** means any work of authorship intentionally submitted for inclusion in the Systems.

**1.6 "Covered File"** means a file that is governed by this License, whether by explicit SPDX header, inclusion in the source tree, or by virtue of being a Modification of an existing Covered File.

**1.7 "Modification"** means any addition to, deletion from, or change to the substance or structure of a Covered File.

**1.8 "Larger Work"** means a work that combines the Systems or any portion thereof with other material in separate files that are not themselves Covered Files.

**1.9 "Distribute"** means to make available to the public or any third party, including as a hosted service, API endpoint, or embedded system.

**1.10 "Invariants"** means the nine ledger invariants I1–I9 as defined in the Meridian v3 specification, incorporated herein by reference. A summary is provided in Appendix C.

**1.11 "Trade‑off Register"** means the versioned, governance‑controlled artifact that states the current position on each contested axis of the Systems.

**1.12 "Maturity Label"** means the classification of any subsystem as `Shipped`, `InDevelopment`, `Research`, or `DeprecatedRemoved`, as defined in the Maturity & Abandonment Ledger.

**1.13 "User"** means any natural person who holds a balance, sends a transaction, earns a contribution credit, or interacts with the Systems as an end‑user.

**1.14 "Race Contract"** means a smart contract encoded via `cross_system_events` that defines a competition to achieve a specified GDP target within a time window, with a governance stake as prize.

